This paper is about object detection using deep learning and visual attention mechanisms. The primary focus is on computer vision (CV) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which suggests that cs.CV and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and sequential actions, which are common in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) research, making cs.LG a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves localization and bounding-box regression, which are relevant to robotics (RO) research. Finally, the paper discusses achieving state-of-the-art performance, which is a common goal in neural networks (NE) research.
